text.text:
If you want a decent or good food but also cheap, then this is the perfect spot for you! (Some of the foods I mentioned isn't in the pics because I forgot)

1. Garlic Bread

One of the best dish I ordered here. It taste good. The only problem is, it's best to eat warm but it took awhile for them to serve it so it's already cold when it reached my table also bake it for a little more time.

2. Pizza

One of the best dish that I ordered, along with garlic bread. The bread dish here are often very delicious and has a good texture. The toppings are just like regular pizza.

3. Non-Spicy Fried Rice (10K)

Reminds me of the blue band fried rice my mom used to make for school lunches.

I like the Umami, buttery taste but it's a little too oily. And no, it doesn't come from butter, it's literally oily. Also I wish there's more to it besides the butter fried rice, scrambled egg and spring onion but the prices were cheap so understandable.

4. Cireng (5-7K ish?)

There's 5, sometimes 6 pieces of it. A bit oily but i like this more than the fried rice. It definitely taste better than some places. It has a bouncy, springy texture but soft inside that I like.

Just wish that it's a little bit more crispy on the outside and the bumbu rujak is not too sweet. (I wouldn't commend the spiciness because I don't handle it well but the sweet taste definitely dominate the sauce)

5. Mini Burger

Bigger than I expected, but there's only 1 burger out of 2 that has a patty. The taste of the burger patty is not bad but it needs more seasoning like salt & pepper and the burger bun is dry. Which is surprising considering one of the best menu in here are involving bread.

Taste wise, it was very very crowded and hot even in Indoor. There's 2 AC but for some reason they only turned on one of them and you can't even feel it. People were gathering at the cashier with a long and messy queue.

The service are inconsistent. Sometimes I was served by a rude/unfriendly employee but other times were very nice/kind and friendly.

Also back then, I often tried to order the hot chocolate and croissant combo but left dissapointed cause it was always unavailable.

All things considered, I think this place is good enough and worth the price. I do believe that you can do something with improving your services, dry bread, seasoning, and oily problem

text.text:
Wasn’t expecting a packed place full of highschool-er and mom with small kids.

I ordered the pizza bread, lemon vanilla bread, and pizza. They came nothing like the picture on the menu. In the menu, the pizza bread looked like baguette with tomato sauce and italian basil on top. What came was bread with tomato sauce and cheese. The bread is lightly toasted, no crunch or crunch texture. All I taste is fluff.

The lemon vanilla was also nothing like the pic. Its only lightly toasted bread with lemon sauce taste like something from Monde canned biscuits. If the bread is crunchy and a bit salty (toasted with butter maybe), it might be better. For the butter would add a bit of salty taste so the whole things doesn’t feel flat.

Their pizza (box) came pretty fast. But the middle of the pizza tasted like the bread hasn’t been baked enough. It tasted like dough with tomato sauce on top.

After all, it all costed less than 50k rupiahs. All 3 bread plus a teh tarik that I ordered only costed me 33k.

I was really disappointed by their service because:
1. The knife they gave me was wet. Dripping wet. Even after i wipe it and when I use it to cut my bread, the water drips to the plate, almost hitting my food. Ew.
2. When I asked for tissue, they only pointing to a tissue dispenser sticking to a wall.
3. The menu book only shows some of the menu, not all. I saw people eating spaghetti but when I make my order they said they dont have creamy spaghetti (as seen on menu). They didn’t mention other spaghetti available like bolognese.

text.text:
A Nice Place to Enjoy Coffee and Stay Awhile

This café really hits the mark when it comes to coffee — it has just the right taste; bold, smooth, and satisfying. It's definitely a place where you can comfortably stay for a long time, whether you're working, studying, or just relaxing.

They offer both indoor and outdoor seating, giving you options depending on your mood or the weather. The atmosphere is inviting and cozy, making it easy to settle in.

The only downside for me was the mix platter. While the taste was good, I was a bit disappointed with the portion size — I had hoped it would be a bit more generous, especially for sharing.

Still, overall it's a great spot for coffee lovers and anyone looking for a chill place to hang out.

text.text:
Welcome to ::Parco:: The Central Perk of Limo (But Cooler, and with Burgers)

Imagine, you’re strolling down the well-known streets of Limo (or Cinere, whatever), mumbling, “Where can I find the perfect spot to escape life’s chaos?” ta-dah! There it is. Bright lights, modern vibes, and a place so inviting even the parking guy would say, “How you doin’?” before walking in.

Step inside, and you will notice this slick, open space that’s basically whispering, “Come work, chill, or pretend to work while you scroll Instagram.” ::Parco:: is like the one of cafes. You are meant to be there.

The place is divided into three sections. Among all your wrong choices you have chosen in your life, don't worry in here you won't 😛

1. The Garden:
Here is the outdoor part. Perfect if you want to puff your cigar or vape without feeling like a smokey monster.
2. The Main Hall:
Tbh, I don't have anything to say about this one. It's just the middle part of the cafe lol.
3. The Air-Conditioned Area:
For those moments when you want to escape the tropical Depok heat that we all know. Unbearable.

You won’t find just your usual coffee shop bites here. Sure, they’ve got the classic western-style dishes, but surprise! You can also order something like Nasi Goreng our Indonesian pride, or Mendoan
My go-to is The burger set. Try it, they have decent kitchen made burgers here.

Do I even need to mention coffee? It’s a cafe, so yes, the coffee’s there, and it’s good enough to keep you buzzing through your meetings or after-work chitchats. Think of it as the Chandler Bing of the menu: reliable, strong, and sometimes just what you need to keep your sarcasm sharp.

As far as I observe, this cafe has already got its loyal customers because anytime I went here, evening or morning, I would always find people taking their seat. Welp, sounds like I am one of them too 😭

Price-wise, it’s not gonna make your wallet scream, maybe a sigh. It’s fair, not dirt cheap, but absolutely reasonable for the quality and atmosphere.

So if you want a place to study, meet clients, hang out, dating, streaming and gaming, napping? wtheck really? welcome! ::Parco:: is calling your name. Trust me, you’ll leave with a full belly, a happy heart, and maybe even a new best friend. Or at least a great story to tell.

🤹 Enjoy your time! And please pet the fluffy cat there 🐈 She's so cute

Step inside, and you will notice this slick, open space that’s basically whispering, “Come work, chill, or pretend to work while you scroll Instagram.” ::Parco:: is like the one of cafes. You are meant to be there.

The place is divided into three sections. Among all your wrong choices you have chosen in your life, don't worry in here you won't 😛

1. The Garden:
Here is the outdoor part. Perfect if you want to puff your cigar or vape without feeling like a smokey monster.
2. The Main Hall:
Tbh, I don't have anything to say about this one. It's just the middle part of the cafe lol.
3. The Air-Conditioned Area:
For those moments when you want to escape the tropical Depok heat that we all know. Unbearable.

You won’t find just your usual coffee shop bites here. Sure, they’ve got the classic western-style dishes, but surprise! You can also order something like Nasi Goreng our Indonesian pride, or Mendoan
My go-to is The burger set. Try it, they have decent kitchen made burgers here.

Do I even need to mention coffee? It’s a cafe, so yes, the coffee’s there, and it’s good enough to keep you buzzing through your meetings or after-work chitchats. Think of it as the Chandler Bing of the menu: reliable, strong, and sometimes just what you need to keep your sarcasm sharp.

As far as I observe, this cafe has already got its loyal customers because anytime I went here, evening or morning, I would always find people taking their seat. Welp, sounds like I am one of them too 😭

Price-wise, it’s not gonna make your wallet scream, maybe a sigh. It’s fair, not dirt cheap, but absolutely reasonable for the quality and atmosphere.

So if you want a place to study, meet clients, hang out, dating, streaming and gaming, napping? wtheck really? welcome! ::Parco:: is calling your name. Trust me, you’ll leave with a full belly, a happy heart, and maybe even a new best friend. Or at least a great story to tell.

🤹 Enjoy your time! And please pet the fluffy cat there 🐈 She's so cute

text.text:
Rarely find bakmi like this in my area and i’m very satisfied. Tried their Bakmi Istimewa, and was mind blown! The Bakmi Istimewa consists 3 toppings (peking duck, steamed chicken and minced chicken). The toppings had their own flavour but blends perfectly when eaten together! You can choose two types of noodles there, i chose the bakmi halus one and it was great.

Also tried their Pangsit Rebus and Bakso Goreng, good for an extra texture and of course delicious! I’d say your bakmi must be accompanied by either one.

Service was good, they know what they’re selling, can do requests for how your noodles liked to be cook, al dente or chewy.

The price was good and surprisingly cheap for this kind of quality of food!

Definitely coming back, or when i don’t have the time, i’ll do online order!

text.text: A good place to go when you need comfort foods 😋

originalText.text: A good place to go when you need comfort foods 😋

text.text:
Amazing, went to eat here after work. Surprised that the items on the menu taste that well despite being priced at near street vendor levels. A must try is the 'tempe mendoan' and 'sosis solo' as snacks or complementary items for the soto.

As for the soto itself, i'm not a huge fan of this type of soto. It's still quite good, but I just don't like how they put too much pete into it and too little meat.
